shared_text:
Merchantville School
July 6 at 1:32 PM ·

Merchantville School has a re-opening committee including representatives from the administration, board of education, teachers, nurses, parents, police and borough council. A survey will be sent out later this week to poll the community on re-opening school in September. The goal is to have a plan in place at the end of July that follows the state guidelines and ensures the best solutions for our students.

Please know that parents set the tone for children. When the plans are announced, read them in private and discuss with other adults in your house. Then come back and tell your children as cheerfully as possible how the Fall will go. Buy or make them a mask that they pick out and tell them how proud you are of them for wanting to keep others safe. Tell them to try their best. They are watching your reaction and will respond accordingly. Even if you are frustrated or upset, the best advice is to be a positive as possible with your child about the upcoming school year. Children do not need to add your worries to their own.

post_text: Thank you to all our families who came out to Pancakes and PJs last night as part of Take Your Family to School Week! A huge thanks goes out to our NJHS students, who set up and served, and the boys’ basketball team, who helped set up before heading off to their game! In addition, special thanks to Amy’s Omelette House, who supplemented us with 3 extra trays of food and provided coupons to our attendees. Our leftover food was delivered to the Niagara Fire Co, who were grateful for the breakfast goodies! Events like these demonstrate that we are part of a wonderful, dynamic, and active community!

Merchantville School
June 11, 2019 at 3:16 PM ·

Merchantville School welcomed back the graduating class from Haddon Heights High School. The returning grads took a "walk down memory lane" by visiting their previous teachers, seeing the school and giving advice to the current Merchantville School students. This is the first full class representing Merchantville School since the phase in began. It continues to be a great relationship between Merchantville School and Haddon Heights.

post_text: Tonight’s Science Expo was a success! Our STEM Escape Room was more challenging—and more humid—than ever, yet all teams thought productively and worked together like champs! Congrats to teams Drama Llama Ding Dong and Taco Cat for escaping the rooms first in their age groups. These groups were made up of 8th grade and 4th grade girls, respectively. Way to show serious girl power! Congrats also to teams Golly GENE and The No-names, who successfully escaped as well. Thank you to all the faculty, staff, families and friends who supported this event and help promote a passion for STEM in our school community!

post_text: Interested in Haddon Heights’ Indoor Guard or Indoor Percussion Program? Heard the buzz about these groups but don’t really know what they do? Have a friend in one of the groups and want to see their AMAZING 2019 competition show? Come out tomorrow night, Thurs 16 May to the Haddon Heights Friends and Family Show to see all 4 groups perform one last time! All the groups just wrapped up their 2019 season two weekends ago with excellent performances at the TIA Atlantic Coast Championships, and would love to perform tomorrow night for a full house. The Friends and Family Show is FREE, and begins at 7:30 pm at Haddon Heights High School.

Hello, families! We need your Box Tops! By clipping these little bits, you can help earn the school hundreds of dollars in FREE MONEY! Here's how to help:
1. Cut the Box Tops carefully, making sure the expiration date and acronym are not obscured.
2. Put the Box Tops in an envelope or bag with your student's homeroom name on it.
3. Send in to school with your student to be turned in to their homeroom teacher.
BOX TOPS ARE DUE FRIDAY, OCTOBER 19th!
Bonus: The class with the most box tops gets an end of the year treat!
